question: ethiopia flight 961 crashes in to the sea
vanilla_rag_result: Ethiopian Airlines Flight 961 crashed into the Indian Ocean on November 23, 1996, after being hijacked by three Ethiopians seeking asylum. The aircraft, a Boeing 767-200ER, was en route from Addis Ababa to Nairobi and ran out of fuel, leading to a crash-landing near Grande Comore, Comoros Islands. Of the 175 people on board, 125 were killed, including the three hijackers.
